### Configure Next.js Edge Runtime for Dynamic Code Evaluation Exceptions

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/07-edge.mdx

This configuration example demonstrates how to use `unstable_allowDynamic` within a `proxy.ts` file to explicitly allow dynamic code evaluation in specific files or directories for the Next.js Edge Runtime. It accepts an array of glob patterns relative to the application root to override the default restriction on `eval` and `new Function`.

```typescript
export const config = {
  unstable_allowDynamic: [
    // allows a single file
    '/lib/utilities.js',
    // use a glob to allow anything in the function-bind 3rd party module
    '**/node_modules/function-bind/**',
  ],
}
```

