### Check for cookie existence on NextResponse (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-response.mdx

Verifies the presence of a cookie by its name on the response using `response.cookies.has(name)`. It returns `true` if the cookie exists and `false` otherwise, providing a simple way to check cookie state.

```ts
// Given incoming request /home
let response = NextResponse.next()
// Returns true if cookie exists, false if it does not
response.cookies.has('experiments')
```

