### Get all cookies or specific cookie values from NextResponse (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-response.mdx

Fetches an array of all cookies on the response using `response.cookies.getAll()`, or an array of cookies matching a given name. Each returned object contains `name`, `value`, and `Path` properties.

```ts
// Given incoming request /home
let response = NextResponse.next()
// [
//   { name: 'experiments', value: 'new-pricing-page', Path: '/home' },
//   { name: 'experiments', value: 'winter-launch', Path: '/home' },
// ]
response.cookies.getAll('experiments')
// Alternatively, get all cookies for the response
response.cookies.getAll()
```

