### Set Cookie on NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Set a cookie with a given name and value on the incoming request. The cookie is added to the Set-Cookie header with the specified path. Useful for setting cookies like banner visibility flags.

```typescript
request.cookies.set('show-banner', 'false')
```

--------------------------------

### Get All Cookies from NextRequest

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-request.mdx

Retrieve all cookies matching a specific name, or all cookies on the request if no name is provided. Returns an array of cookie objects with name, value, and path properties.

```typescript
request.cookies.getAll('experiments')
// Alternatively, get all cookies for the request
request.cookies.getAll()
```

