### Get All Cookies in Next.js Server Component

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/cookies.mdx

Shows how to retrieve all available cookies using the cookies() API and the .getAll() method in a Server Component. Iterates through the cookie collection to display name-value pairs in the UI. Optionally filter by cookie name if specified.

```typescript
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

export default async function Page() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies()
  return cookieStore.getAll().map((cookie) => (
    <div key={cookie.name}>
      <p>Name: {cookie.name}</p>
      <p>Value: {cookie.value}</p>
    </div>
  ))
}
```

