### Set a cookie on NextResponse (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/blob/canary/docs/01-app/03-api-reference/04-functions/next-response.mdx

Uses `response.cookies.set(name, value)` to add or update a cookie in the response's `Set-Cookie` header. This allows server-side control over client-side cookies for managing state or user preferences.

```ts
// Given incoming request /home
let response = NextResponse.next()
// Set a cookie to hide the banner
response.cookies.set('show-banner', 'false')
// Response will have a `Set-Cookie:show-banner=false;path=/home` header
return response
```
